##Method ##

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

##Method void setColor(#SkColor #color) #setColor

Set the #color used by #stroking and #filling. The color is a 32-bit value
packing 8 bit components for alpha, red, blue, and green. The color is #unpremultiplied;
the color's alpha sets the transparency independent of the values of red, blue, and green.

##Table
# bit positions # 31 - 24 # 23 - 16 # 15 - 8 # 7 - 0 ##
#               # alpha   # red     # blue   # green ##
##Table ##

##Param #color    The packed unpremultiplied ARGB color. ##
        
##Example
SkPaint green1, green2;
unsigned a = 255;
unsigned r = 0;
unsigned g = 0;
unsigned b = 0;
green1.setColor(a << 24 + r << 16 + g << 8 + b << 0);
green2.setColor(0xFF00FF00);

##Example ##

#ToDo incomplete ##
#SeeAlso #setARGB #SkColorSetARGB ##

